            <title>[SPARK-45080] Kafka DSv2 streaming source implementation calls planInputPartitions 4 times per microbatch</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-45080</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I was tracking through method calls for DSv2 streaming source, and figured out planInputPartitions is called 4 times per microbatch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It turned out that multiple calls of planInputPartitions is due to `DataSourceV2ScanExecBase.supportsColumnar`, though it is called through `MicroBatchScanExec.inputPartitions` which is defined as lazy, hence shouldn&apos;t happen.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The behavior seems to be coupled with catalyst and very hard to figure out why, but with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-44505&quot; title=&quot;DataSource v2 Scans should not require planning the input partitions on explain&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-44505&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-44505&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we can at least fix this per each data source.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
